              <table id="EditorialReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">Join a team of photographers and two models on a practical workshop  in Majorca for a refreshing look at glamour photography, as they explore both classical  and experimental approaches.  <P>Starting off with a look at the equipment required for a glamour shoot, the authors also  offer practical advice on searching for suitable models. The pictures produced during the  workshop describe the whole process, and compositional considerations are covered next  - the possibilities of camera format and location, and how to frame a figure to achieve  different effects. The first practical session has the participants outdoors, choosing  locations at the pool, on the beach, and in the landscape. The need to plan shots is  emphasised, and this chapter offers plenty of practical advice on how to do this. The  second session sees the team setting up an indoor studio, and gives examples of what can  be achieved through the positioning of lighting and reflectors, and the use of ambient  light. The final chapter discusses what can be done with the images once they have been  shot, examining the range of options with slide film, print film and digital media.  More than 200 shots and 6 portfolios by the participants demonstrate the success of the  workshop, and make this book a real treat for all lovers of modern glamour photography.   <P>Martin Sigrist writes for various photographic magazines, and is the author of many  books on photography. Matthias Stolt is a professional photographers who is  internationally renowned for his fashion, figure and nude images. They both live in  Germany.</span>
              
</td></tr></table>
              <table id="CustomerReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Customer reviews:</DIV>
                
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Very Creative</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
